  "content": "contradiction -- --nocapture`\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia\ngit add crates/corvia-kernel/src/reasoner.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(reasoner): implement TemporalContradiction check across source origins\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3.5: Wire new checks into the Reasoner's `run` method\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `repos/corvia/crates/corvia-kernel/src/reasoner.rs`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add optional `DocsRulesConfig` field to the Reasoner**\n\nThe existing `Reasoner` struct holds 2 fields: `store: &dyn QueryableStore` and `graph: &dyn GraphStore`. Add a new optional field:\n\n```rust\npub struct Reasoner<'a> {\n    store: &'a dyn QueryableStore,\n    graph: &'a dyn GraphStore,\n    docs_rules: Option<corvia_common::config::DocsRulesConfig>, // new\n}\n```\n\nUpdate the constructor to default the new field to `None` (backward compat), and add a builder method:\n\n```rust\npub fn new(store: &'a dyn QueryableStore, graph: &'a dyn GraphStore) -> Self {\n    Self { store, graph, docs_rules: None }\n}\n\npub fn with_docs_rules(mut self, rules: corvia_common::config::DocsRulesConfig) -> Self {\n    self.docs_rules = Some(rules);\n    self\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Add dispatch for new check types in `run_all` / `run_check`**\n\nIn the method that dispatches checks by `CheckType`, add:",
